label.value: negative regulation of programmed necrotic cell death

value.value: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of programmed necrotic cell death.

label.value: positive regulation of programmed necrotic cell death

value.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of programmed necrotic cell death.
Catalysis of the reaction: protein L-aspartate + 2-oxoglutarate + O2 = protein 3-hydroxy-L-aspartate + succinate + CO2.

label.value: female germline stem cell symmetric division

value.value: Division of a female germline stem cell to produce two germline stem cells of the same type as the parent.
Binding to a region of RNA containing a Pumilio-response element element. The consensus sequence for the element is UGUAAAUA.
Catalysis of the reaction: S-adenosyl-L-methionine + RNA = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + RNA containing 2'-O-methylribonucleotide.

label.value: regulation of protein localization to non-growing cell tip

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to a non-growing cell tip.

label.value: negative regulation of protein localization to non-growing cell tip

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to a non-growing cell tip.
Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of DNA recombinase disassembly, the disaggregation of a DNA recombinase complex into its constituent components.

label.value: negative regulation of DNA recombinase disassembly

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of DNA recombinase complex disassembly, the disaggregation of a DNA recombinase complex into its constituent components.
The directed import of zinc(2+) from the cytosol, across an organelle membrane, into the organelle.

label.value: fatty acid primary amide biosynthetic process

value.value: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of a fatty acid primary amide.
The volume enclosed by the membrane of an early phagosome.
A chloroplast-derived plastid in which the solid form of phenol is stored.

A protein complex that associates with chromatin to form linear elements in fission yeast. In S. pombe, the LinE complex contains four main structural components (Rec10, Rec25, Rec27, and Mug20) and other associated proteins.

The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components during meiotic prophase to form a LinE complex, the protein complex that associates with chromatin to form linear elements in fission yeast. In S. pombe, the LinE complex contains four main structural components (Rec10, Rec25, Rec27, and Mug20) and other associated proteins.
The meiotic cell cycle chromosome organization process in which LinE complexes closely associate with chromatin during meiotic prophase to form mature linear elements.

Catalysis of the reaction: S-adenosyl-L-methionine + histone H3 L-lysine (position 37) = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + histone H3 N6-methyl-L-lysine (position 37). This reaction is the addition of a methyl group to the lysine residue at position 37 of the histone H3 protein.
Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of linear element maturation.
Combining with 4-hydroxybutyrte to initiate a change in cell activity.

Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of mitochondrial gene expression. Gene expression is the process in which a gene's coding sequence is converted into a mature gene product (protein or RNA).

label.value: fatty acid primary amide metabolic process

value.value: The chemical reactions and pathways, including anabolism and catabolism, by which living organisms transform primary fatty amides.

label.value: fatty acid primary amide catabolic process

value.value: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of primary fatty amides.

A heterodimer involved in the stabilization of DNA recombination intermediates, the promotion of crossover recombination, and the proper assembly of the synaptonemal complex in meiotic prophase nuclei. In yeast the complex consists of two subunits, Msh4 and Msh5.
Any constituent part of a chitin-based noncellular, hardened, or membranous extracellular matrix secreted from the apical surface of an epithelial sheet.
A extracellular matrix which attaches an organism to a substrate.
Catalysis of the reaction: gluconapin + a reduced electron acceptor + O2 = xi-progoitrin + an oxidized electron acceptor + H2O.
Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of L-glutamine biosynthesis.

label.value: negative regulation of L-glutamine biosynthetic process

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of L-glutamine biosynthesis.

label.value: positive regulation of L-glutamine biosynthetic process

value.value: Any process that starts, increases the frequency, rate or extent of L-glutamine biosynthesis.

A plasma membrane protein complex capable of low-density lipoprotein particle receptor activity. It may also bind xenobiotic toxins and deliver them into the cell via endocytosis. While most substrates get degraded via the endosome the receptor is recycled to the plasma membrane. It may also act as a transducer of intracellular signal pathways and often acts in corporation with other cell-surface receptors.
Any protein complex that is part of a membrane and which functions as a cargo receptor.
The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a light-responsive receptor in a camera-type eye over time, from its formation to the mature structure.
A septin collar in pathogenic fungi involved in the constriction of hyphae at the plant plasmodesma enabling penetration of an adjacent cell.
A protein-containing complex that functions with the RNA exosome and contributes to the degradation of abberant transcripts.
The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of L-beta-ethynylserine. L-beta-ethynylserine is an antibiotic produced by Streptomyces bacteria.
The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of L-propargylglycine (Pra). L-propargylglycine is an antibiotic produced by Streptomyces bacteria.
Catalysis of the reaction: L-2-amino-4-chloropent-4-enoate = chloride + H+ + L-propargylglycine.
Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + L-glutamate + L-propargylglycine = ADP + H+ + L-gamma-glutamyl-L-propargylglycine + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: 4-chloro-L-lysine + AH2 + O2 = A + formaldehyde + H2O + L-2-amino-4-chloropent-4-enoate + NH4(+).
Catalysis of the reaction: 2-oxoglutarate + chloride + H+ + L-lysine + O2 = 4-chloro-L-lysine + CO2 + H2O + succinate.
Catalysis of the reaction: 2-oxoglutarate + L-gamma-glutamyl-L-propargylglycine + O2 = CO2 + L-gamma-glutamyl-(3R)-L-beta-ethynylserine + succinate.

label.value: detection of stimulus involved in sensory perception of pain

value.value: The series of events involved in the perception of pain in which a stimulus is received and converted into a molecular signal.
Catalysis of the reaction:(+)-amorpha-4,11-diene + 3 O2 + 3 reduced [NADPH--hemoprotein reductase] = (+)-artemisinate + 4 H+ + 4 H2O + 3 oxidized [NADPH--hemoprotein reductase].
A protein-containing complex that is capable of catalase activity.
Catalysis of the reaction: a cytidine in mRNA + S-adenosyl-L-methionine = a 5-methylcytidine in mRNA + H+ + S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine.
A protein adaptor that recognizes and binds an RNA molecule modified by C5-methylcytidine.
Catalysis of the reaction: H+ + H2O + N6-methyl-AMP = IMP + methylamine. Can also use N6-methyl-dAMP as a substrate.
A protein-containing complex that serves as a channel for the secretion of curli. Curli are a fibers that serve as a major component of the extracellular matrix of pellicle biofilms.
Enables the ATP-dependent diffusion of a potassium ion across the mitochondrial inner membrane.
